{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Zustand as Cache Layer (Recommended)\n      Zustand owns runtime timer state. React Query still fetches habits, but timer state lives in zustand — not derived from the habits query.\n      \n        Pros\n          \n            Instant UI updates — no waiting for query invalidation\n            Timer state decoupled from habit fetching\n            Easy to read from any component (mini-bar, habits view, etc.)\n            Hydrate once on app load from habits query, then zustand is source of truth\n          \n        \n        Cons\n          \n            Two sources of truth — must keep zustand + DB in sync\n            Need hydration logic on page load\n          \n        \n      \n      Flow: Click Start → zustand updates immediately (optimistic) → API call fires → on success, store confirmed. On failure, rollback store.","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775513657353}
